Show HN: Either your last warning or one of many. Who gives a shit?
text:
This is my latest exhibition of paintings. Hopefully it's in the spirit of HN.

The exhibition overview:

This is either your last warning or one of many. Really, who gives a shit? is that growing uncomfortableness in the (online) air. It’s that feeling where you're compulsively scrolling through disaster after disaster but just can't stop. That internal disappointment when you head into nature for a break but your connection stops things from loading.

Painted with oil paint and mixed media materials, each piece begins entirely on the canvas, without any kind of formal plan. Layers and layers get built upon each other until the painting takes place. The end result is a dirty, heavy canvas filled with texture and bent lines.

The tech: HTML & CSS

Thanks!
